The {{nihongo|'''Special Type 5 Launch To-Ku'''|特五式内火艇 トク|toku-go-shiki uchibitei To-Ku}} was a [[Japan]]ese amphibious [[tank]] built in 1945.{{sfn|Tomczyk|2003|p=32}}

The To-Ku was large and heavy; it boasted extensive armor protection with 50 mm of armor plate in the front hull. The turret was a modified version of the one used on the [[Type 97 Shinhoto Chi-Ha]] medium tank and fitted with a Type 1 25 mm gun and a rear facing [[Type 97 heavy tank machine gun|Type 97 7.7 mm machine gun]].{{sfn|Tomczyk|2003|pp=32, 43}} The front hull mounted a [[Type 1 47 mm tank gun]] and a Type 97 7.7 mm machine gun.{{sfn|Tomczyk|2003|pp=32, 33}} The chassis was based on the [[Type 5 Chi-Ri]] medium tank and the suspension, pontoons and propulsion system were substantially the same as the [[Type 3 Ka-Chi]].{{sfn|Tomczyk|2003|pp=32, 43}} Only one prototype was built of this amphibious tank.{{sfn|Tomczyk|2003|p=32}}

